---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro"
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro"
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro"
import { getRelativeLocaleUrl } from "astro:i18n"

const lang = Astro.currentLocale || "en"
---

<Layout
  title="About the project | 100cosas.dev"
  description="Learn the mission behind 100cosas.dev: a practical collection of software fundamentals to become a better programmer, one tip at a time."
  alternateUrl="/sobre-el-proyecto"
>
  <Navbar alternateUrl="/sobre-el-proyecto" />

  <main id="main-content" tabindex="-1" class="flex-grow w-full">

    <header class="relative overflow-hidden border-b border-white/[0.04]">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-sky-500/[0.04] to-transparent"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[600px] h-[300px] bg-sky-500/[0.03] rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>

      <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-20 pb-16 text-center">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-1 rounded-full border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] mb-8">
          <span class="font-pixel text-sky-400 text-[11px]">100</span>
          <span class="text-neutral-500 text-[11px]">cosas.dev</span>
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-neutral-100 tracking-tight mb-6 leading-[1.15]">
          About the <span class="text-sky-400">project</span>
        </h1>

        <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed max-w-xl mx-auto">
          An initiative by <a
            href="https://midu.dev"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            aria-label="midudev website (opens in a new tab)"
            class="text-sky-400 hover:text-sky-300 transition-colors underline decoration-sky-400/30 underline-offset-2 hover:decoration-sky-300/50">midudev</a
          > to strengthen the foundations of software development.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-16 space-y-12">

      <section class="about-section">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center size-8 rounded-lg bg-sky-500/10 text-sky-400 font-pixel text-xs shrink-0">01</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-neutral-100 tracking-tight">Why this project?</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-11 space-y-4 text-[15px] text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            This project was born out of the need to collect and modernize
            fundamental advice for programmers. It is inspired by the collective
            work <strong class="text-neutral-200">"97 Things Every Programmer Should Know"</strong>,
            adapting its content to an interactive and accessible format.
          </p>
          <p>
            The goal is to offer a roadmap of knowledge that transcends specific
            programming languages and frameworks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="border-t border-white/[0.04]"></div>

      <section class="about-section">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center size-8 rounded-lg bg-sky-500/10 text-sky-400 font-pixel text-xs shrink-0">02</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-neutral-100 tracking-tight">What does it provide?</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-11 space-y-4">
          <p class="text-[15px] text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
            100cosas.dev is not just a list of advice; it is a tool to:
          </p>
          <ul class="grid gap-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
              <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500/60 shrink-0"></span>
              <span><strong class="text-neutral-200">Reflect</strong> on the daily practice of programming.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
              <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500/60 shrink-0"></span>
              <span><strong class="text-neutral-200">Discover</strong> design and architecture principles that are often overlooked.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
              <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500/60 shrink-0"></span>
              <span><strong class="text-neutral-200">Keep a record</strong> of your learning, marking the concepts you already master.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-[15px] text-neutral-400">
              <span class="mt-1.5 size-1.5 rounded-full bg-sky-500/60 shrink-0"></span>
              <span><strong class="text-neutral-200">Multi-language support</strong>: Available in both Spanish and English.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="border-t border-white/[0.04]"></div>

      <section class="about-section">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
          <span class="flex items-center justify-center size-8 rounded-lg bg-sky-500/10 text-sky-400 font-pixel text-xs shrink-0">03</span>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-neutral-100 tracking-tight">Programming in the AI era</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-11 space-y-4 text-[15px] text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            We live in an era where Artificial Intelligence can generate code in
            seconds. However, this makes
            <strong class="text-neutral-200">having solid foundations more important than ever</strong>.
          </p>

          <blockquote class="border-l-2 border-sky-500/40 pl-4 py-1 my-2">
            <p class="text-neutral-300 font-medium italic">
              Why? Because AI is a tool, not a substitute for professional judgment.
            </p>
          </blockquote>

          <p>
            Understanding the "why" behind the code, knowing when a solution is
            scalable, detecting code smells, and applying robust design principles
            is what allows a programmer to guide the AI, rather than being guided
            by it.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong class="text-neutral-200">Foundations are the basis that allow you to discern if what the AI
            generates is really the best solution for your problem.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="border-t border-white/[0.04]"></div>

      <section class="rounded-xl border border-white/[0.06] bg-white/[0.02] p-6 sm:p-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center gap-4 sm:gap-6">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-center size-12 rounded-xl bg-sky-500/10 shrink-0">
            <svg class="size-6 text-sky-400" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M13 2L3 14h9l-1 8 10-12h-9l1-8z" />
            </svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-base font-medium text-neutral-100 mb-1">Ready to start?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
              Explore all 100 tips, track your progress and become a better programmer one step at a time.
            </p>
          </div>
          <a
            href={getRelativeLocaleUrl(lang, "/")}
            class="sm:ml-auto shrink-0 inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-2.5 rounded-lg bg-sky-500/10 text-sky-400 text-sm font-medium hover:bg-sky-500/20 transition-all border border-sky-500/20 hover:border-sky-500/30"
          >
            View tips
            <svg class="size-3.5" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="currentColor">
              <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M2 8a.75.75 0 01.75-.75h8.69L8.22 4.03a.75.75 0 011.06-1.06l4.5 4.5a.75.75 0 010 1.06l-4.5 4.5a.75.75 0 01-1.06-1.06l3.22-3.22H2.75A.75.75 0 012 8z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
